Benefit (DE / EN): Kindergeld (DE) / Child allowance (EN)
IDLB: B100019_LB_576986
Requirements text (EN): The following requirements apply to you as parents:

  * You are subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or are treated as such. This also applies to nationals of the EU, EEA or Switzerland. A domestic residence is not necessarily required.
  * For EU or EEA nationals who moved to Germany after August 2019, additional requirements apply. From the 4th month after entry, the requirements of the Freedom of Movement Act must be met. EU or EEA nationals have freedom of movement if they 
    * are self-employed or employed
    * are job seekers or involuntarily unemployed
    * can derive their freedom of movement from a family member
    * have sufficient means of subsistence and sufficient health insurance coverage or
    * have acquired a permanent right of residence.

  * You are not a citizen of the EU, EEA or Switzerland, but hold a valid settlement permit or a specific residence permit that entitles you to work or
  * You are a legally recognized refugee or entitled to asylum.

Requirements for your child:

  * Your child must have their residence or habitual abode in Germany or in another EU or EEA state or Switzerland.
  * You may also be entitled to child allowance if your child lives in a household in the EU, EEA or Switzerland, for example, if you or the other parent are subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or are treated as such.

Step 2 - Break down the requirements text into individual eligibility requirements. Decide for each requirement whether to include it in the SHACL graph by assigning it one of the following labels: 
    - GREEN: A layperson can easily assess if they meet the condition -> Include
    - YELLOW: A layperson could likely assess if they meet the condition with some explanation -> Include
    - RED: The requirement is ambiguous or is at the discretion of third parties and cannot be clearly assessed -> Exclude

1. User is subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or is treated as such. (GREEN)
2. User is a national of the EU, EEA or Switzerland or has a valid residence permit. (GREEN)
3. EU or EEA nationals who moved to Germany after August 2019 must meet the requirements of the Freedom of Movement Act from the 4th month after entry. (YELLOW: Explanation required)
4. EU or EEA nationals have freedom of movement if they 
    * are self-employed or employed (GREEN)
    * are job seekers or involuntarily unemployed (GREEN)
    * can derive their freedom of movement from a family member (GREEN)
    * have sufficient means of subsistence and sufficient health insurance coverage (GREEN)
    * have acquired a permanent right of residence (GREEN)
5. User is a legally recognized refugee or entitled to asylum. (GREEN)
6. Child must have their residence or habitual abode in Germany or in another EU or EEA state or Switzerland. (GREEN)
7. User or the other parent are subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or are treated as such. (GREEN)

Step 3 - Generate the SHACL graph in Turtle syntax. Model only the GREEN and YELLOW requirements using ontology terms and SHACL Core components. The final answer is:

```turtle
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix ff: <https://foerderfunke.org/default#> .

# METADATA

ff:B100019_LB_576986 a ff:SocialBenefit ;
    rdfs:label "Kindergeld"@de, "Child allowance"@en . 

# CONSTRAINTS

ff:KindergeldShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    ff:checksFundingRequirement ff:B100019_LB_576986 ;
    sh:targetNode ff:User ;
    # User must be subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or be treated as such
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:incomeTaxLiability ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:hasValue ff:UnlimitedTaxLiability ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'User must be subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or be treated as such.'"@en ;
    ] ;
    # User must be a national of the EU, EEA or Switzerland or have a valid residence permit
    sh:property [
        sh:path (ff:isNationalOf | ff:hasResidencePermit) ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'User must be a national of the EU, EEA or Switzerland or have a valid residence permit.'"@en ;
    ] ;
    # User must be a national of the EU, EEA or Switzerland and moved to Germany after August 2019 or have a valid residence permit
    sh:property [
        sh:path (ff:isNationalOf | ff:hasResidencePermit) ;
        sh:qualifiedValueShape ff:EUorEEANationalOrValidResidencePermitShape ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'User is a national of the EU, EEA or Switzerland who moved to Germany after August 2019 or has a valid residence permit.'"@en ;
    ] ;
    # User is a legally recognized refugee or entitled to asylum
    sh:property [
        sh:path (ff:recognizedRefugee | ff:entitledToAsylum) ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:hasValue true ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'User is a legally recognized refugee or entitled to asylum.'"@en ;
    ] ;
    # Child must have their residence or habitual abode in Germany or in another EU or EEA state or Switzerland
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:receivesChildBenefitFor ;
        sh:qualifiedMinCount 1 ;
        sh:qualifiedValueShape ff:ChildShape ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'Child must have their residence or habitual abode in Germany or in another EU or EEA state or Switzerland.'"@en ;
    ] ;
    # User or the other parent are subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or are treated as such
    sh:property [
        sh:path (ff:incomeTaxLiability | ff:closeRelative ff:incomeTaxLiability) ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:hasValue ff:UnlimitedTaxLiability ;
        sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'User or the other parent are subject to unlimited income tax liability in Germany or are treated as such.'"@en ;
    ] .

ff:EUorEEANationalOrValidResidencePermitShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:or (
        ff:EUorEEANationalShape
        ff:ValidResidencePermitShape
    ) .

ff:EUorEEANationalShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:nodeKind sh:Literal ;
    sh:datatype xsd:boolean ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:hasValue true ;
    sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'EU or EEA national.'"@en ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:isNationalOf ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:in (ff:EEAplusCH) ;
    ] ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:uninterruptedLegalStayForLessThan15Months ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:hasValue false ;
    ] .

ff:ValidResidencePermitShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:nodeKind sh:Literal ;
    sh:datatype xsd:boolean ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:hasValue true ;
    sh:message "Does not meet requirement 'Valid residence permit.'"@en ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:hasResidencePermit ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:entitlesToEmployment true ;
    ] .

ff:ChildShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ff:countryOfResidence ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:in (ff:EEAplusCH ff:Germany) ;
    ] .
```

